.TH "jizz-by-theblacklotus" "6" "2026-06-13" "Games" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
\f[B]jizz-by-theblacklotus\f[R] - launch the Jizz 64 KB intro by The
Black Lotus
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]jizz-by-theblacklotus\f[R] [\f[B]\[en]help\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]Jizz\f[R] is a 64 KB intro created by \f[I]The Black Lotus\f[R] and
entered in the intro competition at the Wired\[cq]97 demoparty in 1997.
.PP
The demo requires a 486DX processor and a 320×200 display in 15 or 16
bits per pixel.
For optimal performance, an iP166 processor or faster is recommended,
along with a GUS sound card with 1 MB of RAM and VBE 2.0 support with
linear framebuffer (LFB) access.
.PP
This Debian/Ubuntu package runs the demo using the \f[B]ixalance\f[R](1)
emulator.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\[en]help\f[R]
Display usage information and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R]
Success.
.TP
\f[B]1\f[R]
Invalid argument or usage error.
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[I]/usr/share/jizz-by-theblacklotus/JIZZ.IXA\f[R]
The demo archive used by the ixalance emulator.
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\f[B]ixalance\f[R](1)
